{"lemma":"خَدَماتٌ","slug":"خَدَماتٌ","root":"خ.د.م","root_slug":"خ-د-م","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-د-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10156","n10162","n10163","n10164","n10165","n10166"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَدَمَ (ḵadama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"service, favour","examples":[{"text":"أُرِيدُ مِنْكُمْ خِدْمَةً.","english":"I want a favour from you."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"office"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"official duty"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"work"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"present to a king or superior, gift of homage"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَدَمَ (ḵadama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare خَدَمَ (ḵadama, “to serve”)."},"ipa":["/xid.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10156","headword_ar":"خَدَمَهُ","root":"xdm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidomapN","text_ar":"خِدْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadomapN","text_ar":"خَدْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,) or, as some say, the latter is the inf. n., and the former [though generally used as the inf. n.) is a simple subst., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He served him; did service for him; ministered to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(PS, TA;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahanahu","text_ar":"مَهَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadama biTaEaAmi baTonihi","text_ar":"خَدَمَ بِطَعَامِ بَطْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He served for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in return for, the food of his belly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and A &c. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wgd","text_ar":"وغد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlqamiySu yaxodumu sanapF","text_ar":"هٰذَا القَمِيصُ يَخْدُمُ سَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This shirt will serve,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last, a year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN saxiyfN laA yaxodumu","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ سَخِيفٌ لَا يَخْدُمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flimsy, garment, that will not serve"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last, long;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that will not be serviceable"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Lh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n10162","headword_ar":"خَدْمَةٌ","root":"xdm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidomapN","text_ar":"خِدْمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A space,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"period,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEapN","text_ar":"سَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of the night (JK, K) or of the day: (K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa*omapN","text_ar":"خَذْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xi*omapN","text_ar":"خِذْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,] is a dial. var. thereof. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n10163","headword_ar":"خُدْمَةٌ","root":"xdm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. signifying (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"characteristic denoted by the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadomaA='u","text_ar":"خَدْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axodamu","text_ar":"اَخْدَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in a sheep or goat; (JK, K, TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness in the lower end of the shank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon blackness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) such whiteness resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamap","text_ar":"خَدَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, TA,) or being likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadam","text_ar":"خَدَم"},{"kind":"text","text":", or anklets: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackness upon whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axodamu","text_ar":"اَخْدَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamapN","text_ar":"خَدَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["JK","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n10164","headword_ar":"خِدْمَةٌ","root":"xdm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to some, and inf. n. of 1: accord. to others, a simple subst. [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Service"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pay for service:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but in this sense probably post-classical.]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadomapN","text_ar":"خَدْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n10165","headword_ar":"خَدَمَةٌ","root":"xdm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick and strong, like a ring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is fastened upon the pastern of a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and to which is attached the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariyHap","text_ar":"سَرِيحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thong"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEol","text_ar":"نَعْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern shoe"},{"kind":"text","text":"with which the foot is sometimes protected], (S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which are attached the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAy^iH","text_ar":"سَرَايِح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thongs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nEl","text_ar":"نعل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [it is the n. un. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAmN","text_ar":"خِدَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as below: in the TA, said to be tropical; but this is pro-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":712},{"kind":"text","text":"bably a mistake: the other significations here following are all tropical:] accord. to AA, [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAmN","text_ar":"خِدَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shackles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hobbles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quyuwdN","text_ar":"قُيُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloxaAlN","text_ar":"خَلْخَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An anklet"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (JK, S, Mgh, K;) because sometimes made of thongs, with gold and silver affixed thereon: (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAmN","text_ar":"خِدَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 612.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA@lomamohuwrapK A_iHodaY","text_ar":"كَا@لْمَمْهُورَةٍ اـِحْدَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamatayohaA","text_ar":"خَدَمَتَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a prov. [meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like her who has been dowered with one of her two anklets"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JK, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahomuwrapN","text_ar":"مَهْمُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ring of white a little above the hoof"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse &c.] You say of a horse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu xadamataAni mino xilaAfK","text_ar":"لَهُ خَدَمَتَانِ مِنْ خِلَافٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a whiteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ring of white a little above the hoof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his fore leg"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right fore leg"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and another in his left fore leg"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably a mistake of a copyist for his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left kind leg"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlf","text_ar":"خلف"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [The coll. gen. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the Deewán of the Hudhalees, as stated by Freytag, in the sense of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place where the colour differs, like an anklet, on the foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a whiteness on the foot of a bull, surrounding it like a circle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAmN","text_ar":"خِدَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks"},{"kind":"text","text":"(“striæ”). See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudomapN","text_ar":"خُدْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  [Hence, also,] (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place where each foot comes forth from the trousers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shank;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) because it is the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamap","text_ar":"خَدَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the anklet: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAmN","text_ar":"خِدَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) Hence, in a trad. of Selmán,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna EalaY HimaArK waEalayohi saraAwiylu","text_ar":"كَانَ عَلَى حِمَارٍ وَعَلَيْهِ سَرَاوِيلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waxadamatAhu tu*abo*ibaAni","text_ar":"وَخَدَمَتاهُ تُذَبْذِبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was upon an ass, and upon him were trousers, and his shanks were dangling"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, as some say, the meaning here is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the parts from which his two feet came forth, of the trousers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodati AlHarobu Eano","text_ar":"اَبْدَتِ الحَرْبُ عَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAmi Almuxad~araAti","text_ar":"خِدَامِ المُخَدَّرَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The war made apparent the shanks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the anklets, of the girls that had been kept behind the curtains"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the war became vehement."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b6-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ring"},{"kind":"text","text":"of people; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compact ring"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: likened to the thong described in the first sentence of this paragraph. (TA.) Hence the saying of Khálid Ibn-El-Weleed, in a letter that he wrote to the Satraps of Persia, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamodu lil~`hi Al~a*iY faD~a","text_ar":"الحَمْدُ لِلّٰهِ الَّذِى فَضَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamatakumo","text_ar":"خَدَمَتَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Praise be to God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who hath dispersed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken up, your congregation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K, * TA:) for when the thong above mentioned is broken, or parted, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAy^iH","text_ar":"سَرَايِح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or thongs of the leathern shoe] become loosed, and the shoe falls off: so says IAth, and A'Obeyd says the like. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n10166","headword_ar":"خَدِمَةٌ","root":"xdm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thong:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plaited thong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]}]}}